    "Finally, Section 4 addresses the asymptotic limit as α ↘ 0 in the particular -but still relevant -case when the proliferation function P (φ) is constant, providing a detailed proof of convergence to the corresponding system with α = 0 (see Theorem 4.1).",
    "Moreover, we are able to prove an estimate of the difference of solutions in suitable norms with a precise rate of convergence (cf.",
    "Theorem 4.3).",
    "General setting and well-posednessIn this section, we introduce the general setting of our problem and state well-posedness results for the state system (1.1)-(1.5).",
    "To begin with, for a Banach space X we denote by ∥ • ∥ X the norm in the space X or in a power thereof, and by X * its dual space."
